The course is taught over two terms. It gives an overview of the main ways of Estonian word formation and how the words are written; Estonian sentence structure and punctuation; critical areas and language innovation. Theoretical material is illustrated with examples and exercises. Special attention is paid to typical mistakes in primary students' language use.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide future primary teachers with the holistic view of Estonian word formation and syntax and integrate theoretical knowledge with didactic skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course a student will know the main ways of Estonian word formation; know if the words are written as one word or separately; can use correct punctuation in atypical sentences; will be familiar with linguistic innovation; can recognise students' mistakes and analyse them.
